By Lukman Olabiyi  Please enable JavaScript This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. Following the truck accident that occurred at Ojuelegba on Sunday, 29th January, 2023, the Lagos State Government has visited the families of the victims who lost their lives. Assuring them of the state government’s commitment to bring to book all parties culpable in the avoidable incident, the delegation expressed the heartfelt condolences of the Governor and the entire people of Lagos State. The delegation led by management of the Ministry of Transportation reiterated that the owner and driver of the ill fated truck will be prosecuted based on the forensic investigation carried out by the Government, adding that justice will be served. The families were happy to receive the delegation saying they appreciate the sympathy conveyed during this time of deep grief.